# Swift Struct Location Rule

All Swift `struct` types MUST be located inside the `/Models` directory.

Constraints:
- NEVER create `struct` definitions inside `/Views`, `/ViewModels`, `/Services`, or `/Networking`.
- If a new struct is required, create a new file inside `/Models`.
- The file name MUST match the struct name.
- Each file SHOULD contain only one primary struct.

Purpose:
Structs represent data models and must be centralized inside `/Models`
to keep the project structure predictable.
